When you send a message to the customer, you can include a unique ID in the message body, and store the ID along with the message details in your database. Then, when the customer replies to the message, you can extract the `previousMessageId` from the incoming message and use it to look up the corresponding message in your database. This way, you can track the conversation history and associate each reply with the correct message.

Here's an example of how to modify the Lambda function code to use `previousMessageId`:
```php
use App\Models\Message; // assuming you have a Message model in your Laravel app

function sendSms($to, $message, $messageId)
{
    // Send the SMS message via AWS SNS
    $sns = new SnsClient([
        'version' => 'latest',
        'region' => 'us-east-1',
    ]);

    $params = [
        'Message' => "$message\n$messageId",
        'PhoneNumber' => $to,
        'MessageAttributes' => [
            'AWS.SNS.SMS.SMSType' => [
                'DataType' => 'String',
                'StringValue' => 'Transactional'
            ],
            'AWS.SNS.SMS.SMSOriginationNumber' => [
                'DataType' => 'String',
                'StringValue' => '+1234567890' // replace with your SMS origination number
            ],
        ]
    ];

    try {
        $result = $sns->publish($params);
        return true;
    } catch (SnsException $e) {
        return false;
    }
}

function handleIncomingSms($event)
{
    $message = $event['Records'][0]['Sns']['Message'];
    $messageId = $event['Records'][0]['Sns']['MessageId'];
    $sender = $event['Records'][0]['Sns']['MessageAttributes']['AWS.SNS.SMS.SMSSender']['Value'];

    // Extract the previous message ID and reply message from the incoming message
    preg_match('/^(.+)\n(.+)$/s', $message, $matches);
    $previousMessageId = $event['Records'][0]['Sns']['MessageAttributes']['previousMessageId']['Value'];
    $replyBody = $matches[2];

    // Look up the corresponding message in your database
    $previousMessage = Message::where('message_id', $previousMessageId)->first();

    // Create a new message with the reply
    $message = new Message();
    $message->to = $previousMessage->from;
    $message->from = $previousMessage->to;
    $message->body = $replyBody;
    $message->message_id = $messageId;
    $message->save();

    // Send an acknowledgement message to the customer
    $responseBody = "Thanks for your reply! Your message ID is $messageId.";

    // Send the acknowledgement message back via SMS
    sendSms($sender, $responseBody, $messageId);

    return response()->json(['status' => 'success']);
}
